The Dockerfile is used for enhancing an existing image installing not included packages
The docker-compose.yml is used as an alternative to run a container with a command

Execute docker-compose 
> docker-compose up

Parameters in shellscript are referenced by a number, for instance $1 means first parameter passed next by the script execution

Parameters in python are accessed by sys module, they are referenced as a list. First element is the script name
so first argument is referenced by index 1, for instance sys.argv[1]